CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 25, 1958, pg.1 reads: " "Vacate The Houses" - Assistant City Solicitor H. Steward Dunn, Building Inspector J. Clyde Taylor and his assistant, Rudy Vaughn, maintain that the Winfield St. apartments of Alfred E. Davis are unfit and unsafe for human habitation and must be vacated.  The city officials obtained Judge O'Brien's sanction for their order. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Assistant City Solicitor H. Steward Dunn, Building Inspector J. Clyde Taylor, and Rudy Vaughn, standing in hallway of Allegheny County Courthouse
